The paper deals with improving the security of cognitive radio multicast communications, which involves information theory (cs.IT), communication and network security (cs.CR), and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of jamming noise, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and systems and control (cs.SY) categories.
